{"id":32225,"date":"2019-06-16T15:16:35","date_gmt":"2019-06-16T11:16:35","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=32225"},"modified":"2025-03-14T22:22:34","modified_gmt":"2025-03-14T18:22:34","slug":"salaam-arrives-leaves","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/06\/16\/salaam-arrives-leaves\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Salaam: Greet with peace arriving and leaving"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Abu Huraira reported: A man passed by the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, while he was sitting in a gathering. The man said, \u201cPeace be upon you.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>Ten good deeds<\/strong>.\u201d Another man passed by, saying, \u201cPeace be upon you and the mercy of Allah.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>Twenty good deeds<\/strong>.\u201d Another man passed by, saying, \u201cPeace be upon you, the mercy of Allah, and His blessings.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>Thirty good deeds<\/strong>.\u201d A man stood up to leave the gathering and he did not offer salutations of peace. The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>How quickly your companion forgets! If one of you comes to a gathering, let him greet them with peace. If there is room for him to sit, let him sit. If he stands to leave, let him offer salutations of peace. The former duty is no different than the latter<\/strong>.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: al-Adab al-Mufrad lil-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 986<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <strong><em>Sahih<\/em><\/strong> (authentic) according to Al-Albani<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0647\u064f\u0631\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0631\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0623\u064e\u0646\u0651\u064e \u0631\u064e\u062c\u064f\u0644\u0627 \u0645\u064e\u0631\u0651\u064e \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0649 \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627